<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb98a3337-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s3102"><num value="3102">§ 3102.</num><heading> Authority to issue search warrant—(Rule)</heading><note id="idb98a3338-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<heading style="-uslm-lc:I71" class="centered"><inline class="small-caps">See Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure</inline></heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0 fontsize7">Federal, State or Territorial Judges, or U.S. magistrate judges authorized to issue search warrants, Rule 41(a).</p>
</note>
<sourceCredit id="idb98a3339-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/819">62 Stat. 819</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/90/578/tIII/s301/a/4">Pub. L. 90–578, title III, § 301(a)(4)</ref>, <date date="1968-10-17">Oct. 17, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1115">82 Stat. 1115</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/101/650/tIII/s321">Pub. L. 101–650, title III, § 321</ref>, <date date="1990-12-01">Dec. 1, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/5117">104 Stat. 5117</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb98a333a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb98a333b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb98a333c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1968—<ref href="/us/pl/90/578">Pub. L. 90–578</ref> substituted “magistrates” for “Commissioners”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb98a333d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I78" topic="changeOfName" id="idb98a333e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Change of Name</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">“U.S. magistrate judges” substituted for “U.S. magistrates” in text pursuant to <ref href="/us/pl/101/650/s321">section 321 of Pub. L. 101–650</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s631">section 631 of Title 28</ref>, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idb98a333f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1968 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/90/578">Pub. L. 90–578</ref> effective <date date="1968-10-17">Oct. 17, 1968</date>, except when a later effective date is applicable, which is the earlier of date when implementation of amendment by appointment of magistrates [now United States magistrate judges] and assumption of office takes place or third anniversary of enactment of <ref href="/us/pl/90/578">Pub. L. 90–578</ref> on <date date="1968-10-17">Oct. 17, 1968</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/90/578/s403">section 403 of Pub. L. 90–578</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s631">section 631 of Title 28</ref>, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
